Rugby pitch, volleyball court and basketball court are not complete too.The 4,500-seater pavilion, sanitation and the changing rooms are already complete.Once complete, the stadium which will be the first in the region will have a football pitch, a rugby pitch, an athletics track, a volleyball court and a basketball court. Deadline for the completion of works at Sh247 million Kirubia Stadium in Tharaka Nithi County has now been extended to the end of February 2021.
Construction of the stadia began on September 23, 2016 and the project was expected to have been finished in 2017, but the government has been giving false promises to the over-anxious sportsmen and women in the region.



