The wall was built by Chuka/Igambang’ombe constituency office using National Government Constituency Development Fund earlier before the work was handed over to the national government Ministry of Sports.
The contractor is also doing the final touches on the tartan track, goal posts not erected on the football pitch, the main gate not fixed and some cabro work still ongoing.
Rugby pitch, volleyball court and basketball court are not complete too.
The 4,500-seater pavilion, sanitation and the changing rooms are already complete.
Once complete, the stadium which will be the first in the region will have a football pitch, a rugby pitch, an athletics track, a volleyball court and a basketball court. The party has told the DP Ruto-led Tangatanga political wing to brace for a bruising campaign. Team is preparing for upcoming 2021 African Nations Championship (Chan) tournament. Senate approved the Bill without amendments, paving the way for Presidential assent.